&lt;h2&gt;ASSEMBLY ASSOCIATE&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;APPARATUS is a New York-based designer and manufacturer of a distinctive catalog of high-end, high-touch lighting, furniture and objects. We produce both in-house and with the support of high-quality external partners; our catalog is sold globally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is responsible for hand-assembling and wiring fixtures in our Brooklyn production facility with a high level of skill and within production timelines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform production duties, including: precision wiring and assembly according to work instructions, operational and functional testing, and prepare products, as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce consistent and high-quality work, on-time and according to department standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn new products and techniques.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meet the output and quality goals.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate with department leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a clean, organized and safe workspace; contribute to overall department organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comply with all Company policies.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support company initiatives and projects on an as-needed basis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SKILLS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intermediate-level assembly, wiring and electrical testing skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trained in electrical safety protocols, quality control inspection, and care and handling standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to accurately read and follow work instructions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to quickly learn and retain knowledge through instruction and hands-on practice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly skilled manual dexterity, use of hand tools and electrical testing equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to perceive color and texture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid problem-solving skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meticulous attention to detail and organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate a positive commitment to feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to routinely raise arms over head, reach, bend and regularly lift up to 50 pounds (and occasionally more).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work standing for an extended period of time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to climb a ladder.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to wear appropriate protective equipment and abide by safety policies and guidelines while working with any hazardous materials/equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reliable and trustworthy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EXPERIENCE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Craftsperson with a desire to learn and grow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in a high-paced environment that values service, efficiency, and output.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma or GED.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;WORK SCHEDULE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
