&lt;h2&gt;SENIOR PRODUCT DESIGNER&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;APPARATUS is New York-based design studio that explores the relationship of lighting, furniture and objects in immersive environments, threading the historical and the cultural through a modern lens. The studio is headed by Gabriel Hendifar, Artistic Director, whose vision drives the studio’s design work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Industrial Designer is responsible for engineering the full range of APPARATUS products, including new and existing lighting, furniture, objects, custom fixtures and special projects. We are a studio of continual refinement. This role requires master-level skills in SolidWorks and an extensive background in engineering with specific prior experience in lighting. Candidate must enjoy working in a collaborative environment, have a solutions-based perspective, be flexible and achieve results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement the vision of the Artistic Director through a broad range of responsibilities including 2D ideation sketching, 3D modeling (SolidWorks), rendering, full scale drawing, prototyping, samples build.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the design engineering of custom lighting and furniture. Responsibilities include designing, prototyping, red-lining production drawings, components QC, dry-fitting production parts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and implement expertise to meet design requirements for UL, CB, CE, UKCA compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide timely and accurate redlines and feedback to vendors in new developments and counter-sourcing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with APPARATUS Interiors department on cross-functional product design needs such as signage, display items, products for spaces and events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accountable for accurate and complete technical drawings that meet evolving internal standards and are clear to globally based vendors and internal manufacturing team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure timely updates and accuracy of live models of permanent collection fixtures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the standards and organization/file management of the team’s internal server.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the Manufacturing department vets all new product design and construction during established checkpoints, implementing their feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide detailed hand-off and of new product from development to production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide hands-on assistance with gallery installations, product maintenance, photoshoots and trade events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Give technical guidance for the manufacturing and sales teams as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support management team in leadership and continuous refinement of team practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor junior team members, setting the standard for best practices for the Product department.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster positive and productive work relationships with those inside and outside the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consider cost implications of work process and projects to ensure prudent spend.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SKILLS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Master-level ability: SolidWorks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in: AutoCAD, Keyshot, Adobe Creative Suite.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Well-developed aesthetic sense and eye for detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Up-to-date knowledge of lighting and manufacturing technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in working for an Artistic Director-led company with a specific vision and vocabulary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background in the facilitation/creation of wiring schematics and voltage calculations for LED lighting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Broad knowledge of materials and techniques including woodworking, metal machining, casting, welding, plastics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent work ethic, demonstrated by a high level of output; ability to self-motivate; ability to manage priorities with a sense of urgency.&lt;/li&gt;
